Toolkit​. To configure OpenCode to use NaviGator Toolkit, you need to create a configuration file in either the global directly of `~/.config/opencode/opencode.json` or your project directory. To select the NaviGator AI models, while in OpenCode use the `/models` command. OpenCode is a powerful terminal-based AI coding agent that brings AI assistance directly to your command line. `opencode run \"Review the user_auth.py file for security issues and suggest improvements\"`.", "score": 0.78650844, "raw_content": "![NaviGator](/img/logo.png)\n![NaviGator](/img/logo.png)\n\n# **OpenCode**\n\n![](/img/toolkit/opencode/opencode_logo.png)\n\nOpenCode is a web-based code editor that integrates AI models directly into the browser. It can be used to edit code, run scripts, and interact with AI models in real-time. OpenCode can be configured to use [NaviGator Toolkit](https://api.ai.it.ufl.edu/ui) as a provider allowing you to get your own AI coding assistant.\n\n## Installing OpenCode[​](#installing-opencode \"Direct link to Installing OpenCode\")\n\n**NPM**\n\n`npm install -g opencode-ai`\n\n**Bun**\n\n`bun add -g opencode-ai`\n\n**Homebrew**\n\n`brew install anomalyco/tap/opencode`\n\n**Linux**\n\n`curl -fsSL https://opencode.ai/install | bash`\n\nToo Install on Windows you should use WSL2 and follow the Linux instructions above or use the NPM or Bun methods.\n\nOnce installed you can launch by running `opencode`\n\n`opencode`\n\n![open code launch](/assets/images/opencode_main-b5bad7339796e37eb4f55fa714368b32.png)\n\n![open code launch](/assets/images/opencode_main-b5bad7339796e37eb4f55fa714368b32.png)\n\n## Configure OpenCode to use NaviGator Toolkit[​](#configure-opencode-to-use-navigator-toolkit \"Direct link to Configure OpenCode to use NaviGator Toolkit\")\n\nTo configure OpenCode to use NaviGator Toolkit, you need to create a configuration file in either the global directly of `~/.config/opencode/opencode.json` or your project directory. The file should be named `opencode.json` and should contain the following:\n\n`~/.config/opencode/opencode.json`\n`opencode.json`\n`{  \n \"$schema\": \"https://opencode.ai/config.json\",  \n \"model\": \"navigator/mistral-small-3.1\",  \n \"provider\": {  \n \"navigator\": {  \n \"npm\": \"@ai-sdk/openai-compatible\",  \n \"options\": {  \n \"baseURL\": \"https://api.ai.it.ufl.edu/v1\",  \n \"apiKey\": \"<[NAVIGATOR_API_KEY](https://docs.ai.it.ufl.edu/docs/navigator_toolkit/getting_started/quickstart#create-an-api-key)>\"  \n },  \n \"models\": {  \n \"mistral-small-3.1\": {}  \n }  \n }  \n }  \n}`\n\nThis configuration files will get you started with the `mistral-small-3.1` model. You can change the model to any other model available in NaviGator Toolkit. For a list of available models, see the [NaviGator Toolkit Models](https://docs.ai.it.ufl.edu/docs/navigator_models/) page.\n\n`mistral-small-3.1`\n\nTo select the NaviGator AI models, while in OpenCode use the `/models` command.\n\n`/models`\n\n![open code model selection](/assets/images/opencode_model_selection-3dc9ebe27579714b9e5143091b685787.png)\n\n![open code model selection](/assets/images/opencode_model_selection-3dc9ebe27579714b9e5143091b685787.png)\n\n## How to Use OpenCode[​](#how-to-use-opencode \"Direct link to How to Use OpenCode\")\n\nOpenCode is a powerful terminal-based AI coding agent that brings AI assistance directly to your command line. Unlike IDE-integrated tools, OpenCode is designed for developers who prefer terminal workflows and need AI assistance that integrates seamlessly with their existing command-line tools and scripts.\n\n### Key Features & Capabilities[​](#key-features--capabilities \"Direct link to Key Features & Capabilities\")\n\n`--continue`\n`--session`\n`-m, --model`\n\n### Common Use Cases & Examples[​](#common-use-cases--examples \"Direct link to Common Use Cases & Examples\")\n\n#### 1. Code Review & Analysis[​](#1-code-review--analysis \"Direct link to 1. Code Review & Analysis\")\n\n**Example**: *\"Review this Python module for best practices and potential issues\"*\n\n`opencode  \n# In the interactive TUI:  \n# \"Analyze the user_auth.py file for security vulnerabilities and code quality issues\"`\n\nOr use direct message mode:\n\n`opencode run \"Review the user_auth.py file for security issues and suggest improvements\"`\n\nOpenCode will:\n\n#### 2. Debugging & Problem Solving[​](#2-debugging--problem-solving \"Direct link to 2. Debugging & Problem Solving\")\n\n**Example**: *\"Help me debug why my tests are failing\"*\n\n`opencode  \n# In the interactive session:  \n# \"Run the test suite and help me understand what's failing and why\"`\n\nOr for quick debugging:\n\n`opencode run \"My React tests are failing with 'Cannot read property of undefined'. Help me debug this.\"`\n\nOpenCode can:\n\n#### 3. Documentation Generation[​](#3-documentation-generation \"Direct link to 3. Documentation Generation\")\n\n**Example**: *\"Generate comprehensive API documentation for my Express.js routes\"*\n\n`opencode  \n# In the TUI:  \n# \"Create API documentation for all routes in the routes/ directory\"`\n\nOr as a direct command:\n\n`opencode run \"Generate OpenAPI documentation for my Express.js API endpoints\"`\n\nOpenCode will:\n\n#### 4. Feature Implementation[​](#4-feature-implementation \"Direct link to 4. Feature Implementation\")\n\n**Example**: *\"Add authentication middleware to my Node.js API\"*\n\n`opencode  \n# Interactive session for complex implementations:  \n# \"Implement JWT-based authentication middleware with proper error handling\"`\n\nOpenCode can:\n\n#### 5. GitHub Integration & Repository Management[​](#5-github-integration--repository-management \"Direct link to 5. GitHub Integration & Repository Management\")\n\n**Example**: Working with GitHub repositories\n\n`opencode github  \n# Access GitHub-specific agent for repository operations`\n\nThis allows you to:\n\n### Terminal Workflow Examples[​](#terminal-workflow-examples \"Direct link to Terminal Workflow Examples\")\n\n#### Quick Code Analysis[​](#quick-code-analysis \"Direct link to Quick Code Analysis\")\n\n`# Start OpenCode and analyze a specific file  \nopencode  \n> \"Analyze the performance bottlenecks in database.py and suggest optimizations\"`\n\n#### Batch File Processing[​](#batch-file-processing \"Direct link to Batch File Processing\")\n\n`# Process multiple files with a single command  \nopencode  \n> \"Add proper error handling to all Python files in the src/ directory\"`\n\n#### Integration with Git Workflows[​](#integration-with-git-workflows \"Direct link to Integration with Git Workflows\")\n\n`# Review changes before committing  \nopencode run \"Review the files I've changed in this commit for any issues\"`\n\nOr use interactive mode for detailed review:\n\n`opencode --continue  \n# \"Please review my recent changes and suggest improvements before I commit\"`\n\n### Best Practices for Terminal-Based AI Coding[​](#best-practices-for-terminal-based-ai-coding \"Direct link to Best Practices for Terminal-Based AI Coding\")\n\n#### Effective Command Usage[​](#effective-command-usage \"Direct link to Effective Command Usage\")\n\n#### Integration with Existing Workflows[​](#integration-with-existing-workflows \"Direct link to Integration with Existing Workflows\")\n\n`opencode run`\n`--continue`\n\n#### Managing Large Projects[​](#managing-large-projects \"Direct link to Managing Large Projects\")\n\n`opencode github`\n\n### Getting Started Tips[​](#getting-started-tips \"Direct link to Getting Started Tips\")\n\n`opencode run`\n`opencode github`\n\n### Example Terminal Session[​](#example-terminal-session \"Direct link to Example Terminal Session\")\n\n`$ opencode  \nOpenCode AI Agent  \n> \"My React app isn't rendering the user list component. Help me debug this.\"  \n  \n[OpenCode analyzes your project structure]  \n[Identifies potential issues in component files]  \n[Suggests running specific commands to diagnose]  \n  \n> \"Run npm